$ System.Data.Common.DbTransaction (class)

An instance of `System.Data.Common.DbTransaction` (or one of its derived classes) allows to commit or roll back a pending → development/databases/SQL/transaction[transaction].

Such an object is returned by calling `BeginTrasaction()` on an object that derives from → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbConnection[`System.Data.Common.DbConnection`].

The two important methods of `DbTransaction` are `Commit()` and `Rollback()`.

